    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/35001605/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The aim of this course is to provide academic and professional communication skills in English, in the field of architecture, starting at a B2 level according to the classification of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR). It is intended to improve the student's competitive ability in English to facilitate their subsequent access to the job market. The program includes: learning technical vocabulary, practicing debates on architectural topics, participating in workshops to help improve essay writing and oral presentations, etc. All these activities are developed both individually and in teams. The four English language skills are put into practice, following the recommendations of the CEFRL.

The course provides students with the necessary skills to introduce themselves as future professionals, and talk about the areas of expertise they would like to specialise in and the type of projects they would like to work on. It also prepares students for the job market and, particularly, provides them with the necessary tools to look for a job of their interest. Additionally, the course provides students with technical vocabulary about architecture and important guidelines to successfully describe architecture projects, both in a written way and orally.

This semester we introduced two new communicative activities (being communication the main objective of this course, hence its name) for which our students had to work with students from two different universities: SeAMK (Seinajoki University of Applied Sciences, Finland) and FH Münster (Münster University of Applied Sciences, Germany). The objective of the first task was to present in teams, in front of Business students from SeAMK, the fictitious architecture studios that we had asked our ETSAM students to set up at the beginning of the course. The activity was developed in groups of two teams (one from the ETSAM and another one from SeAMK) so that the Finnish students could give the Spanish ones feedback on how to make their architecture studios economically viable. In the second place, the task our students had to carry out with their counterparts from the School of Architecture of Munster was related to the implementation of the Sustainable Development Goals proposed by the European Union. In this case, the ETSAM students had to teamwork with students from Munster School of Architecture so that all of them could learn from each other regarding recent projects carried out in Spain and Germany that are good examples of SDGs implementation. This last task is also related to Dr. Martín Castillejos¿ personal compromise to spread out the values of the United Nation as a UPM member of EELISA-ESCE (Community: Ethics, Social Commitment & Entrepreneurship). Both tasks were communicative experiences, where students had to use specific language and where the final purpose was to make them think about how to make their future architecture studies economically profitable and how to develop themselves professionally by building sustainable architecture in terms of use of materials, energy consumption, etc."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/paloma.ubeda%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/am.martin.castillejos%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/ester.gimenez%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/paloma.ubeda%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Comunicacion Oral y Escrita en Lengua Inglesa"@es .

