<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/35001605/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """CONTINUOUS ASSESSMENT
The continuous assessment will consist of three tasks and two tests:
1. Task: Professional writing (to be submitted via Moodle where students will find further instructions).
2. Task: Architectural project description / architectural essay (to be submitted via Moodle where students will find further instructions).
3. Task: Oral presentations (detailed instructions will be provided via Moodle).
4. Specific vocabulary (ESP for Architects)
5. Listening test (multiple choice).

FINAL EXAM
The exam will be divided into 5 sections:
1. Terminology (2p): Exercise(s) about architecture-related specific vocabulary. There could be matching, multiple-choice or fill-in-the-gaps exercises.
2. Grammar (2p): Multiple-choice or fill-in-the-gaps grammar exercises.
3. Writing (2p): You will be asked to write either a cover letter/résumé applying for a real job offer or the description of a given architecture project.
4. Listening (2p): You will watch a video or listen to a recording twice, and you will be asked to answer a number of multiple-choice questions.
5. Speaking (2p): The oral test can include topics such as introducing yourself personally and professionally, answering job interview questions, or describing an architecture project."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/35001605/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
